sentences: Tuuli Rand (born 1 March 1990 in Kuressaare, Saaremaa) is an Estonian singer.
With Liisi Koikson and band Söörömöö (of it she is a member), she sang the song "Üle vee" (Over the Water) and as a solo artist sang the song "Ring the Alarm", with Teele Viira.
Rand participated in Eesti Laul 2021 to represent Estonia in the Eurovision Song Contest 2021 with her song "Üks öö", but did not qualify for the final.
